						<summary>

						<p>A broken slab built into the wall of the southern gate of Jama masjid.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Sōmēśvara II 11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record engraved on two faces of a broken slab contains the genealogy of the Chālukya kings (of Kalyāṇa) of which Trailokyamalla, Somēśvara II and the latter's younger brother are mentioned.</p>						

						<p>Much of the information is lost as the top and sides of the slab are broken and lost. It is in characters of the 11th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
